##a3c1ad|**Larry Cumbleton##**: Hey guys, the holidays are coming. 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart##**: Uh huh.

##green|**Leonora Morales##**: Uh huh.

##red|**Tony Catalano##**: Uh huh.

##a3c1ad|**Larry Cumbleton##**: What kind of attitude is this, where are y’all’s holiday spirits? Or don’t you guys throw parties at this Site? 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart##**: We do.

##green|**Leonora Morales##**: We do.

##red|**Tony Catalano##**: We do.

##a3c1ad|**Larry Cumbleton##**: Hey, stop repeating yourselves like bots. What’s happening? Director? 

##blue|**Vincent Bohart##**: The Foundation gave us homework this year. 

##a3c1ad|**Larry Cumbleton##**: And I thought you guys should be happy about this? Like, if things were going as usual, we would be completely abandoned, right?

##red|**Tony Catalano##**: If we put it that way, then why would the Foundation give us an urgent mission this year, you dickhead? We’re probably fucking doomed. 

##green|**Leonora Morales##**: Oh come on Tony, he’s new, don’t be so heavy on him. But yeah, what’s up with you, really?

##a3c1ad|**Larry Cumbleton##**: As far as I remember, all the people at my internship said that holiday missions are a piece of cake, like secret gift exchange or Site-wide decorating for fun and stuff.

##blue|**Vincent Bohart##**: Cheese in the trap. 

##green|**Leonora Morales##**: Cheese in the trap. 

