**Description:** SCP-005-VN is Ronnie Peterson, a famous Swedish racer also formerly known as “SuperSwede”. SCP-005-VN is a Resurrection Entity[[footnote]]Resurrection Entities are human beings, animals or any organism capable of thoughts returning from a “forever afterlife” through anomalous means. The entities themselves are bound to resurrection with a problem to be solved, or a mission to be completed [...] In addition, they are given “blessings” from the world above, or more plainly speaking, anomalous properties. ~ Excerpt from "Looking Up To The World Above: A Deep Research Into Resurrection.", Sam Jones, PhD, SCP Foundation Journal of Parascience, Volume 286, Issue of April 1^^st^^ (2021), internal circulation. [[/footnote]] Level III, possessing minor anomalous properties such as indestructible physique, heat resistance and resistance to certain common diseases.

Besides, SCP-005-VN also possesses SCP-005-VN-1 as a transportation vehicle. 

[[collapsible show="Update Christmas 2023" hide="Hide Update"]]

**Updated Description:** At present, SCP-005-VN-1 is a modified Formula 1 racing car. SCP-005-VN-1’s paint depicts an instance of //Rangifer tarandus// (Reindeer) in a sprinting position on its front half, with its forelegs placing on the two front wheels and its rear legs pushing on the rear wheels, as well as a pair of antlers painted on its front wings.

SCP-005-VN-1’s minimum speed equals the maximum speed of a normal Formula 1 car, and its maximum recorded speed exceeds Mach 2.5. SCP-005-VN-1 also has the ability to completely control its sound level, which prevents nearby civilians from being woken up during the nights that SCP-005-VN fulfills its obligations. It is theorized that SCP-005-VN-1 appeared as an effort to “catch up with modern trends”.
